sect1.para:
When does the continued acceptance of bullying workplace behaviors become too extreme? Should it be after an employee is openly verbally accosted in front of their fellow employees? Or a physical assault occurs after numerous reports of witnessed verbal bullying and “light shoves” in the hallway while the bully passes by the affected person. When a person or persons submit a notice of resignation to their employer after weeks, months, or years of experiencing workplace bullying? Or, Perhaps it is when an actual suicide has occurred after the person affected by workplace bullying just could not tolerate another day, hour, minute, or second with being bullied. The affected person in the case of a suicide feels helpless and hopeless after being unheard and ignored by their employer and fellow employees (Howard et al., 
               2021
            ).
